The paper focuses on developing a machine learning-based solution for scheduling multi-robot teams in manufacturing environments. This involves addressing combinatorial optimization problems with temporal and spatial constraints. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI, which deals with artificial intelligence and machine learning. The paper also involves robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY) as it deals with coordinating multi-robot teams. The use of deep Q-learning and graph attention networks also suggests a focus on deep learning (cs.LG) and mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
